<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Habitus as depicted in Figs 4c, 5c. Clypeus with anterior margin rounded (Fig. 6a). Reticulation of dorsal surface confined to head, more distinct and impressed anteriorly. Punctation of head fine, visible on whole surface; punctures sparse, distance between them usually equal or bigger than their diameter (Fig. 6a). Punctation of pronotum double, fine, distance between larger punctures bigger than their diameter. Punctation of elytra double, diameter of small puncture less than half of diameter of large punctures; distance between large punctures bigger than their diameter. Epipleura smooth with fine punctures. Metatibia with sinuous outer margin.</paragraph>
<caption pageId="1" pageNumber="74">
