<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="75" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="75">
The species inhabits various types of standing water, predominantly densely vegetated pools, ditches and small ponds. 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. anatolicus" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="anatolicus">H. anatolicus</taxonomicName>
tolerates also saline habitats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="75" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="75">The species is distributed in the Eastern Mediterranean and in south-eastern Europe. It occurs in Italy, southernmost Slovakia, Hungary, the Balkan Peninsula, Turkey, southern Ukraine and Russia up to latitude 55° and east to the Ural Mountains (Fig. 9). First record from Slovakia and Ukraine.</paragraph>
